\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Do you think this mystery moment is a good idea, or should we just leave it at the levity ending?}
\par\plain \f0\fs26\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs26\b0\i0 Below is a draft of what I was thinking ending the scene with. The reader will have to turn the page to  find out why the door opened before sarah knocked  and who was on the other side of the door. Let me know your thoughts and rewrite my sentence into something more compelling and usable:}
